data.name: Label2.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the preinstallation environment for Windows Live OneCare Rewritten by "Cobs".
Installation Notes:
-If you're attempting a reinstall after a failed initial install, please delete %temp%\OCSetup and c:\OneCare -Windows XP is not supported yet. -Backup is known to cause a "not installed" message. -V2.5 Discs cause missing file 'dw20sharedamd64.cab' error. This is being worked on.
Requirements: -Microsoft .Net 4.0 -Windows Vista -Windows Live ID Assistant Service -Windows Live OneCare disc in optical drive or virtually mounted

data.name: Label9.Text
data.value:
Reviewing Microsoft's warning, all assets including the original OneCare logo and the installer banner are protected by copyright.
Unauthorised Reproduction or re-distribution of them could lead them to potentially sue me which I don't want.
I do realise this new installer makes things look very industrial, but it's for my own protection to keep this project alive.

data.name: Label8.Text
data.value:
As much as I'd love to say yes, absolutely not.
This installer mimics what the real installer would do if you manage to pass the initial "Checking for updates" screen.
Unfortunately due to Microsoft taking down the software in 2009, it seems the servers went with it. This makes installing it (even from a disc) impossible with the built in installer.
This project aims to remedy that by installing everything required.
If you find bugs, please let me know. I can't promise anything but I'll try my best to resolve them.
Backup (PXEngine) doesn't work. I'm looking into this.

data.name: Label5.Text
data.value:
When you're ready to install. Place the Microsoft Live OneCare Disc into your optical drive. If autorun shows, close it.
Remember if any additional setup wizards ask you to restart the PC, choose No. You'll get a screen similar to this when we're ready to restart.
That's it. Push Install below!

data.name: Label11.Text
data.value:
Looking to uninstall Windows Live OneCare from your computer?
This installer unfortunately cannot do this.
However, this can be achieved from control panel. Click the button below to launch Programs and Features so you can uninstall OneCare.
